brood /bruːd/

(brooding,brooded,broods) 

1. N-COUNT A brood is a group of baby birds that were born at the same time to the same mother. 一窝幼雏 

例： ...a hungry brood of fledglings. …一窝饥饿的雏鸟。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to someone's young children as their brood when you want to emphasize that there are a lot of them. 一家子 [强调] 

例： ...a large brood of children. …一大家子小孩。 

3. V-I If someone broods over something, they think about it a lot, seriously and often unhappily. 担忧 

例： She constantly broods about her family. 她一直在为她的家人担忧。

